# Next.js 14 App Router

## Server Components (Default)

- Use Server Components by default (async components for data fetching)
- Only add `'use client'` directive when necessary:
  - Component uses React hooks (useState, useEffect, etc.)
  - Component needs browser APIs
  - Component has interactivity/event handlers
- Keep Server Components async for data fetching
- Minimize client boundaries - pass data from Server to Client Components via props

## Data Fetching

- Use `fetch()` directly in Server Components with appropriate cache options:
  - `cache: 'force-cache'` for static data (default)
  - `cache: 'no-store'` for dynamic data
  - `next: { revalidate: N }` for ISR
- Colocate data fetching with components when possible
- For client-side data fetching, always use React Query (see React Query rules)

## Route Files

- Use `loading.tsx` for loading states
- Use `error.tsx` for error boundaries
- API routes: `app/api/*/route.ts`
  - Implement proper error handling and status codes
  - Validate inputs using Zod schemas
  - Return consistent response formats
  - Use middleware for auth checks

## Server Actions

- Use Server Actions for mutations when appropriate
- Always validate inputs in Server Actions
- Handle errors gracefully
